<subSubSection id="C37945B24922FFDAFE86FE8BFBABDBEC" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFD9FE86FE8BFE56DE62" blockId="5.[264,664,283,345]" box="[264,392,319,345]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
(
<figureCitation id="13580ABC4922FFD9FE9FFE8BFE5EDE62" box="[273,384,319,345]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–5" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[295,1304,895,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-219@5.[271,1316,884,1694]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 4–5. Chrysosoma ruyuanense sp. nov. (Male). 4. Left It1, ventral view; 5. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050271/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFD9FE86FE3BFB6ADEEA" blockId="5.[264,1323,399,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis. Antenna brownish yellow; frons with group of 5–6 long thick pale hairs on postero­lateral slope; FI with row of long pale ventral hairs (as long as width of FI).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFD9FEB6FE6BFBEADEC2" blockId="5.[264,1323,399,825]" box="[312,1076,479,505]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Description. Male body length 
<quantity id="4C9BBBDC4922FFD9FD2BFE6BFCEADEC2" box="[677,820,479,505]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.65" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="5.65" valueMax="5.9" valueMin="5.4">5.4–5.9 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="4C9BBBDC4922FFD9FC5DFE6BFBEEDEC2" box="[979,1072,479,505]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFD9FEB6FDB3FC8FDC02" blockId="5.[264,1323,399,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; vertex distinctly excavated, frons subshining. Hairs and bristles on head black; middle and lower postocular bristles (including postero­ventral hairs) pale; frons with 1 pvt and 1 group of 5–6 long thick pale hairs on postero­lateral slope, ocellar tubercle with 2 long strong oc. Antenna brownish yellow; scape somewhat swollen; pedicel with circlet of apical bristles (including 2 long ventral bristles); first flagellomere triangular, nearly as long as wide; arista apical, blackish except narrow base brown, slightly longer than head + thorax. Proboscis dark yellow with brownish hairs; palpus dark yellow with brownish hairs.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1C46B14922FFD9FE86F92AFEAED9E5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050271" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5050271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050271/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" startId="5.[264,382,1694,1718]" targetBox="[295,1304,895,1682]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFD9FE86F92AFEAED9E5" blockId="5.[264,1322,1693,1758]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B917CA2B4922FFD9FE86F92AFE6BD98D" bold="true" box="[264,437,1693,1719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">FIGURES 4–5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C636DBA4922FFD9FE33F92BFD1AD98D" authority="Zhu &amp; Yang, 2005" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2005" box="[445,708,1695,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruyuanense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B917CA2B4922FFD9FE33F92BFD1AD98D" box="[445,708,1695,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Chrysosoma ruyuanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22477504922FFD9FD45F92BFCC0D98D" box="[715,798,1695,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Male). 4. Left It 
<subScript id="17E7147C4922FFD9FC54F91AFC3FD980" attach="left" box="[986,993,1710,1723]" fontSize="5" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">1</subScript>
, ventral view; 5. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394922FFDAFEB6F8A0FD57DDCC" blockId="5.[264,1324,1812,1878]" lastBlockId="6.[264,1325,284,1239]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on thorax black; 2 strong posterior dc and 3 anterior hairs; 3 long irregularly paired acr; scutellum with 2 pairs of sc, basal pair very short and hair­like. Legs yellow brown; CI yellow, CII and CIII blackish; t 
<subScript id="17E7147C4921FFDAFE0CFEE0FE49DE59" attach="left" box="[386,407,340,354]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">2­5</subScript>
brown. Hairs and bristles on legs black; coxae with pale hairs; CI with 2 yellow spine­like apico­lateral bristles. Femora with long pale ventral hairs: FI with row of long pale ventral hairs (as long as width of FI); FII and FIII with row of short pale ventral hairs on basal half (as long as width of FII and FIII). TI with 1 short ad at basal 1/7, apically with 1 short bristle; TII with 1 long strong ad at basal 1/5, 3 av and 1 pd at basal 1/3, apically with 3 long bristles; TIII with 1 long ad at basal 1/6, 10 av and 9 pd, apically with 2 long bristles. TI apical 1/4 and It 
<subScript id="17E7147C4921FFDAFD23FDF3FD6BDD6E" attach="left" box="[685,693,583,597]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">1</subScript>
basal half somewhat flattened with very short dense ventral pubescence (
<figureCitation id="13580ABC4921FFDAFE77FDD6FD9CDD47" box="[505,578,610,636]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–5" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[295,1304,895,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-219@5.[271,1316,884,1694]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 4–5. Chrysosoma ruyuanense sp. nov. (Male). 4. Left It1, ventral view; 5. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050271/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Relative lengths of tibia and tarsomeres: LI 3.2: 2.6: 0.9: 0.7: 0.4: 0.3; LII 3.9: 3.5:?:?:?:?; LIII 4.0: 3.3:?:?:?:?. Wing: hyaline, tinged with brown; veins dark brown, M 
<subScript id="17E7147C4921FFDAFD9EFD76FDC6DDEB" attach="left" box="[528,536,706,720]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">1</subScript>
concave, crossvein m­cu straight. Squama dark yellow. Halter brownish yellow with pale knob.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394921FFDAFEB6FCB1FDB4DC7C" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1239]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Abdomen dark metallic green with gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on abdomen black, but sterna 1–2 with pale hairs.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394921FFDAFEB6FCE1FB3ADC84" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1239]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13580ABC4921FFDAFE76FCE1FD9ADC54" box="[504,580,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–5" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[295,1304,895,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-219@5.[271,1316,884,1694]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 4–5. Chrysosoma ruyuanense sp. nov. (Male). 4. Left It1, ventral view; 5. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050271/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Epandrium distinctly much longer than wide with 1 lateral hair; surstylus rather thick with 3 apical bristles, basally with a short lateral process; hypandrium rather thick with narrow left lateral arm; aedeagus thick; cercus furcate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC16394921FFDAFEB6FC79FDC6DCDC" blockId="6.[264,1325,284,1239]" box="[312,536,973,999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
